tion advisor roles) with Schedule C 1099 income across multi-client engagement portfolios, and PE-backed consolidating consulting firms with rollover equity post-acquisition. Bain and Company unique structure with employee ownership through ESOP (Employee Stock Ownership Plan) established 2006 differentiating Bain from McKinsey and BCG private partnerships. Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 variable income with 24-month average for MBB W-2 + signing + bonus and Accenture W-2, B3-3.1-09 other sources for Accenture and tier 2 publicly listed RSU continuing vesting and Bain ESOP equity participation, B3-3.4-02 partnership and S-corporation analysis for MBB and Big 4 consulting partner K-1 with Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks at partnership level, B3-3.3-02 self-employed Schedule C analysis with Form 1084 cash-flow addbacks for independent consultants and fractional CFO multi-client portfolios. Conventional Conforming, Conventional Jumbo, Conventional Super-Jumbo, Multi-Source W-2 + RSU (Accenture Managing Director), S-Corp Self-Employed, Schedule C + Form 1084, and Bank Statement Non-QM loan program options. Consulting services is explicitly Specified Service Trade or Business (SSTB) under IRC Section 199A with QBI deduction phase-out at higher income (parallel SSTB treatment to legal and accounting). MBB up-or-out promotion structure with substantial promotion-tied raises context, MBB elite tier dominance and premium positioning, Accenture publicly listed scale dominance, Big 4 consulting practice growth, boutique proliferation and Fractional CXO trend, PE acquisition wave of mid-tier consulting, and AI / automation pressure on entry-level consulting industry dynamics." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/professional-services/consultants/">
